The Catholic church was on rue Caumartin, close to Printemps and Galeries Lafayette.

A very beautiful Catholic church known in the lively rue de Caumartin. A church serving everyone, open all day to meet the needs of the faithful and passers-by by offering seven daily masses, the presence of numerous priests providing confessions and various spiritual activities to form and renew one's faith.
a quiet church despite the location of very noisy streets. Very pretty indoors and outdoors. Very pleasant. A little small for a visit but it was still nice!
Almost non-stop confessions, frequent adoration and eucharist in the heart of Paris near Saint-Lazare in a beautiful church. Praying Church.

Very central church in Paris, right in the middle of the Saint Lazare district between Printemps and Galeries Lafayette. Many masses during the day either in French (for the most part) or in Latin, and confessions all day long, with an average of two priests. Often a lot of queues at confessions during "peak hours", that is to say around noon, and from 4/5 p.m., and therefore a lot of waiting which can sometimes go up to 45 minutes (and therefore even sometimes it is not possible to confess because it is too late). In off-peak times we wait on average 10 minutes. On the other hand the church is very pretty, well maintained, and the altars on the side aisle are dedicated to beautiful devotions such as Our Lady of course, the Little Jesus of Prague, Saint Teresa of the Child Jesus, saint Michael, Saint Anthony of Padua....
Magnificent church for those who want to find a little peace in the tumult of Paris.

Very beautiful parish church has two entrances outside Caumartin neo-classical style or rue du Havre very contemporary style.  Built in 1783 under Louis XVI for the Capuchin convent of which only the Condorcet high school remains.  Many faithful, 7 daily masses are celebrated, many priests provide confessions and a range of spiritual activities from reception.  Marcel Proust was baptized there and continued his studies at the nearby Condorcet high school.
Very beautiful church, a haven of peace in the heart of a neighborhood full of shops.

A church with a warm interior including the presence of a very beautiful alcove with lots of candles on the left. Ambience collected but welcoming and open. Remarkable ceiling and paintings. I recommend the (free) visit. Guitarist and singer priest with good atmosphere on a music festival day. Church recognized for its welcome of the poorest and stateless people.
